  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong> over a low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until the onion has softened&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>noodles</strong> to a pot of boiling water (enough to cover them) with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Boil for 3 min or until starting to soften</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, trim the <strong>green beans</strong> and cut them in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the same pot as the&nbsp;<strong>noodles</strong> and cook for a further 3 min</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and rinse the lot briefly under cold water (to prevent them from sticking together and continuing to cook) before returning them to the pot (off the heat)</p>\r\n<p>Trim the fat off the<strong> pork steaks</strong>&nbsp;and slice finely into strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pork strips</strong> to the <strong>onion pan</strong>, increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 4 min, then cover with a lid and cook for a further 2 min or until the pork has cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and keep covered until later (this stops the pork overcooking)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>sesame oil</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>sugar</strong> and half the <strong>spring onion</strong> in a bowl - this is your <strong>chilli mixture</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/515.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
